---
// The 200 MB ceiling is ONLY for whole-doc edit/export/validate.
---
<section class="block">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="scale-grid">
      <div class="iv">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="tick"></span>Built for big</span>
        <div class="scale-stat" style="margin-top:24px"><em>GB</em><span class="un">+</span></div>
        <div class="scale-body" style="margin-top:24px">
          <p>Most editors choke at a few hundred megabytes. Pandia opens files of
          <strong>any size</strong> — hundreds of MB, multiple GB — without parsing the whole
          tree: lazy <strong>zero-copy slicing</strong> engages at <strong>≥&nbsp;10&nbsp;MB</strong>
          (backed by <strong>sonic-rs</strong>) and the UI only ever fetches the slice on screen.</p>
          <p>You scroll, search, and navigate instantly — there's <strong>no cap on opening or
          viewing</strong>. Only whole-document edit, export and validate materialize the root
          (a 200&nbsp;MB ceiling).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scale-points">
          <div class="pt"><span class="lbl">Lazy mode</span><span class="gn">≥ 10 MB</span> &nbsp;zero-copy slicing engages</div>
          <div class="pt"><span class="lbl">Opening</span><span class="gn">any size</span> &nbsp;multi-GB, no lag, no cap</div>
          <div class="pt"><span class="lbl">200 MB cap</span>only whole-doc edit / export / validate</div>
          <div class="pt"><span class="lbl">Recovery</span>auto-save &amp; backups, scan / restore</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="iv">
        <div class="meter">
          <div class="meter-head">
            <span class="nmf">users-2026-05.json</span>
            <span class="sz">1.2 GB · 109,472 records</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meter-body">
            <div class="meter-row">
              <span class="ml">Open</span>
              <span class="bar"><i class="good" style="width:14%"></i></span>
              <span class="mv">instant</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meter-row">
              <span class="ml">First paint</span>
              <span class="bar"><i class="good" style="width:22%"></i></span>
              <span class="mv">virtualized</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meter-row">
              <span class="ml">In memory</span>
              <span class="bar"><i class="accent" style="width:34%"></i></span>
              <span class="mv">lazy slice</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meter-row">
              <span class="ml">Binary</span>
              <span class="bar"><i class="good" style="width:9%"></i></span>
              <span class="mv">Rust + Tauri</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style is:global>
  .pandia-page .scale-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 64px; align-items: center; }
  .pandia-page .scale-stat {
    font-family: var(--disp); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.045em;
    font-size: clamp(72px, 10vw, 132px); line-height: 0.86; color: var(--page-text);
  }
  .pandia-page .scale-stat em { font-style: normal; color: var(--accent); }
  .pandia-page .scale-stat .un { font-size: 0.34em; color: var(--page-dim); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .pandia-page .scale-body p { font-family: var(--disp); font-size: 16.5px; color: var(--page-dim); line-height: 1.65; }
  .pandia-page .scale-body p + p { margin-top: 16px; }
  .pandia-page .scale-body strong { color: var(--page-text); font-weight: 600; }
  .pandia-page .scale-points { margin-top: 28px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-top: 1px solid var(--page-rule); }
  .pandia-page .scale-points .pt {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; padding: 13px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--page-rule);
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--page-dim);
  }
  .pandia-page .scale-points .pt .lbl { color: var(--page-faint); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 10px; width: 132px; }
  .pandia-page .scale-points .pt .gn { color: #4e8a3a; }

  .pandia-page .meter { border: 1px solid var(--app-rule-2); overflow: hidden; background: var(--app-elev); color: var(--app-text); }
  .pandia-page .meter-head {
    height: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 0 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--app-rule); font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--app-dim);
    background: var(--app-elev-2);
  }
  .pandia-page .meter-head .nmf { color: var(--amber); }
  .pandia-page .meter-head .sz { margin-left: auto; color: var(--app-faint); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 10px; }
  .pandia-page .meter-body { padding: 20px 18px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; }
  .pandia-page .meter-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; }
  .pandia-page .meter-row .ml { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--app-faint); width: 104px; }
  .pandia-page .meter-row .bar { flex: 1; height: 6px; background: var(--app-elev-3); overflow: hidden; position: relative; }
  .pandia-page .meter-row .bar i { position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0; }
  .pandia-page .meter-row .mv { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--app-text); white-space: nowrap; text-align: right; flex-shrink: 0; padding-left: 4px; }
  .pandia-page .bar i.good { background: var(--green); }
  .pandia-page .bar i.accent { background: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 940px) { .pandia-page .scale-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .pandia-page .scale-grid { gap: 40px; }
    .pandia-page .scale-points .pt { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px 10px; align-items: baseline; }
    .pandia-page .scale-points .pt .lbl { width: 100%; }
    .pandia-page .meter-head .sz { display: none; }
    .pandia-page .meter-row .ml { width: 82px; }
  }
</style>
